article.description: Grant Senne kicked a 35-yard field goal with 2:06 left to help Brown beat Holy Cross 25-24 on Saturday.
article.headline: Late field goal lifts Brown over Holy Cross 25-24
article.linkText: Late field goal lifts Brown over Holy Cross 25-24
article.story: WORCHESTER, Mass. -- Grant Senne kicked a 35-yard field goal with 2:06 left to help Brown beat Holy Cross 25-24 on Saturday. Senne's kick capped an 11-play, 63-yard drive -- the big play coming on a 14-yard completion from Marcus Fuller to Alexander Jette on third-and-six to the Holy Cross 24. Peter Pujals hooked up with Jake Wieczorek for a 5-yard touchdown pass early in the third to give Holy Cross to a 24-22 lead. It stayed that way until Senne's game-winner. Fuller was 33 of 50 for 412 yards. Jette had 16 catches for 216 yards -- both career highs. Troy Doles added nine catches for 112 yards. Brown (2-2) went up 8-0 in the first on a pair of Senne field goals and a safety. Andrew Coke's 4-yard rush made it 15-3, but Pujals found Blaise Bell and Brendan Flaherty on short touchdown passes and the Crusaders (2-3) trailed 22-17 at intermission.
